      • SUPER_ROOT

        public static final VertexLabel SUPER_ROOT
        Technical node (just one), ancestor of resources. This vertex is only part of data model, it is not present in object domain model (except of persistence layer). Super root is the root of the stored metadata. Hence, all userâ€™s metadata are below super root in the vertex hierarchy. In the database exists only one vertex of this type. Super root has only one property superRoot. This property has no other usage than as a single-property index.

      • SOURCE_ROOT

        public static final VertexLabel SOURCE_ROOT
        Technical node (just one), ancestor of sources. This vertex is only part of data model, it is not present in object domain model (except of persistence layer). Source root is the root of the tree with source nodes. In the database exists only one source root. Source root has only one property sourceRoot. It is a single-property index for quick search of the source root.

      • REVISION_ROOT

        public static final VertexLabel REVISION_ROOT
        Technical node (just one), ancestor of revisions (revision vertexes). This vertex is only part of data model, it is not present in object domain model (except of persistence layer). Revision root is the root of the tree with revision nodes. In the database exists only one revision root. Revision root has only one property revisionRoot. It is a single-property index for quick search of the revision root.
